  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-white/5">
    <div class="muted text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-6">
      <strong class="text-ink-100">Provenance:</strong> ASHRU is built on the six kāraka case roles formalized in
      Pāṇini's <em>Aṣṭādhyāyī</em> (~5th century BCE). It is humanity's grammar — public domain by virtue of
      being 2,500 years old. Named in honor of <strong class="text-ink-100">Ashrith</strong>; in Sanskrit, अश्रु
      ("ashru") is the distilled essence — a tear that holds the whole.
    </div>
